# Phase 6: React Frontend

## Purpose
Build an interactive web interface for the semantic search system. Users will be able to search for jobs, apply filters, view results, and discover similar jobs and companies - all through a modern, responsive UI.

## Why React + TypeScript?
- **React**: Most popular frontend framework, large ecosystem, component-based
- **TypeScript**: Type safety catches bugs early, better IDE support, self-documenting
- **Vite**: Fast build tool, instant HMR, better than Create React App

## Key Features

### 1. Search Interface
- Search bar with query input
- Filter panel (collapsible on mobile)
- Results grid/list with job cards
- Pagination or infinite scroll

### 2. Job Card Component
- Title, company, salary range
- Skills tags
- Posted date badge
- Similarity score indicator
- "Find Similar" button

### 3. Filter Panel
- Salary range slider
- Employment type checkboxes
- Region/location dropdown
- Company search
- Clear filters button

### 4. Similar Jobs
- "Find Similar" opens modal or sidebar
- Shows top 5-10 similar jobs
- Option to exclude same company

### 5. Company Similarity
- Company search input
- Shows similar companies with stats
- Job count, avg salary, top skills per company

